Package: simple-screen-capture
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Kerry Ritter <kerry@example.com>
Depends: rofi, maim, ffmpeg, xclip, optipng, xbindkeys,
 python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, libnotify-bin, x11-utils
Recommends: pulseaudio-utils
Description: Screenshot, GIF and screencast capture with a floating menu
 Trigger a floating rofi menu via Ctrl+Shift+Alt+R to:
  - Take area screenshots copied to clipboard as Base64 or binary PNG
  - Record area GIFs with palette-optimised colour
  - Record area screencasts as MP4 (with optional audio)
 .
 All captures use a persistent resizable region selector so the capture
 area is visible before recording begins. Run capture-setup after install
 to wire up the keyboard shortcut.
